28/05/2010
PRISTINA, Kosovo -- The government of Kosovo and the IMF signed an agreement Thursday (May 27th) on a 110m-euro loan "with very favourable conditions", Prime Minister Hashim Thaci said.
The loan would ensure a growth rate of 6% for the country, he added.
At a press conference in Pristina, Thaci said the loan "also opens a path, and includes the promised donations from the EU and the World Bank of 210m euros in next three years".
(Xinhua, AFP - 27/05/10)
